# Cursor IDE Rules

**For complete documentation, read [CLAUDE.md](CLAUDE.md) and [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md).**

CLAUDE.md is the single source of truth for this project.

## Quick Reference

**Framework**: Nuxt 3/4 + Vue 3.5 + @nuxt/content
**Source**: All code in `src/`
**This is a boilerplate** - content files are examples

## Essential Commands
```bash
npm run dev                      # Start dev server
npm run build                    # Production build
npx vitest run                   # Run tests
npx eslint src --ext .ts,.vue    # Lint code
npm run lint:css                 # Lint CSS (if exists)
npm run validate:tokens          # Validate tokens (if exists)
```

## Standards (See CLAUDE.md for details)
- Vue: `<script setup lang="ts">` composition API
- Components: PascalCase, `ccm` prefix for DS
- TypeScript: 2-space indent, no semicolons, single quotes
- CSS: CUBE methodology, design tokens, `--_ccm-{component}-{property}`

## Project Structure
```
src/
├── pages/          # File-based routes
├── components/ds/  # Design system (ccm*)
├── composables/    # Composition utilities
├── content/        # Markdown (examples)
├── public/         # Static + CSS
├── server/         # API routes
└── tests/          # Vitest specs
```

